Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you donâ€™t have symptoms.

Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Seychelles. See information on measures introduced in Seychelles to limit the spread of the virus.
Many airlines are cancelling, changing or reducing their inward and outward flight schedules.
You should urgently contact your airline or tour operator to confirm travel arrangements if you are due to travel to or from Seychelles.
The British High Commission team is available to offer advice between 07.30 and 19.30 (local time, Seychelles) every day of the week on a dedicated extended telephone service which can be reached on +248 260 0451.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
